casebody.data:
BROWNE, Appellant, v. BAKER et al., Respondents. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. February 16, 1894.) Action by Mary A. Browne against John M. Baker and another.

Argued before VAN BRUNT, P. J., and O’BRIEN and FOLLETT, JJ.

Jerome A. Nason, for appellant. W. E. Stiger, for respondents.

No opinion. Motion to dismiss appeal granted, with $10 costs. See 26 N. Y. Supp. 1113.
